FT  11 JUN 92 / Perth glass maker bought by Fullers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Perth-based glass manufacturing business of John Moncrieff has been
bought out of receivership by Fullers Investments.
John Moncrieff, which employs 41 people making engineering and scientific
glassware and high-performance lenses, had been in receivership for 14
weeks. The business will be carried on under the name of Monax Glass.
