more than 50 per cent of the net assets in March and their listings were
largely responsible for the rise in net asset value.
A final and exceptional dividend amounting to Pounds 235,000, payable as a
result of the receipt of non-repeatable dividends, was approved after
publication of the results to September 30 1991.
However the actual amount of dividend per share cannot be calculated until
it is known how much loan stock will be converted to shares on June 30.
Earnings per share came out at 0.46p (4.36p).
