would be a reshuffle of some military district commanders.
The new deputy ministers are to be 'new people' - leaving no room for
deputies from the formerly Soviet and now so-called Commonwealth defence
ministry. Gen Grachev said they would be selected on a 'democratic' basis -
from multiple candidates who were presently in Moscow for the final
selection procedures.
But it is also clear that President Yeltsin will be looking for people whose
loyalty he can rely on most at a time of political instability, and low
morale within the armed forces.
