independent companies that repair Kodak copiers and printers.
They charged that Kodak had violated federal anti-trust law by refusing to
sell replacement parts to owners of Kodak equipment unless they agreed not
to do business with independent service companies. It was alleged that this
illegally tied the sale of one product to a separate condition or service.
