</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A BILL aimed at conserving British fish stocks received its second reading
in the Commons last night despite being opposed by three rebel Tory MPs,
David Owen writes.
Opposition to the measure by Mr David Harris, the MP for St Ives, Mr David
Porter (C Waveney) and Mr Robert Hicks (C Cornwall South East), helped
