<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 92 / Five Tube lines miss targets
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FIVE OF London Underground's 11 lines have failed to meet the performance
targets announced by the government last month. On the system as a whole, on
average, 97.5 per cent of scheduled rush-hour trains were run.
The worst performer was the Victoria Line, which failed to run nearly 20 per
cent of scheduled rush-hour trains in the four weeks to May 22. Top
performer was the East London Line, which ran all its rush-hour trains.
London Underground blamed a long-standing matter of irregular wear on
trains' wheels, which was probably caused by faulty lubrication.
