Grace's board. It is expected to take three to four months to complete.
Grace said that by divesting non-core businesses it would be able reduce its
debt load.
The division, based in Massachusetts, produces chemical intermediates used
in cosmetic and personal care products, soaps and detergents,
pharmaceuticals, water treatment and other applications.
