satisfied by an initial payment of Pounds 1.1m and a further maximum Pounds
100,000 depending on stock valuation and cost cuts.
Sales for the six months to March 31 fell from Pounds 7.12m to Pounds 6.38m
reflecting the recession and the impact of discontinued businesses. However,
Mr Jeremy French, chairman, said that margins were maintained.
Earnings per share came out at 1.47p (1.63p); the interim dividend is held
at 1.45p.
